HEADWORD: autogyro
<hw>autogyro</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an aircraft that is supported in
flight by unpowered rotating horizontal wings (or blades); forward
propulsion is provided by a conventional propeller.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> autogiro, gryoplane</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

